				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Is it possible ?<a name="55237"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 5 04 7:37 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The answer is pretty much no.
<br />

<br />
We have an All-Bard guild on FV server, which we made pretty much with the sole purpose of stretching and finding out what Bards could pull off working together.  Basically, if a mob has any ONE of the following characteristics, it CAN be solod or killed by Bards:
<br />

<br />
Charmable
<br />
Mezzable
<br />
Fearable
<br />
Non-Summoning
<br />

<br />
Any one of those four things makes a mob vulnerable to Bards.  If it has NONE of those characteristics (Named Dragons have none of these), and the mob hits hard, then you pretty much HAVE to have a healer and a real tank.  (MAYBE having lots of healing power and a Bard tanking, lol.)</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=564823">Scherzo Glissando </a><BR>
Maestro, Molto Espressivo</span></td>
