				<td colspan="2"><span>If by named dragons you mean Trak, Yeli and Zlandi, the answer is no, but if you mean named dragons like the weaker ones in Western Wastes then absolutely yes. A lot of bards use charm to throw pets at tough targets, but you have to realize that even if you're using a pet the mob will still summon you and get some good whacking in, no matter how fast you can run. This gets compunded when you have a pet and get summoned, then the charm breaks. If you have good gear and get buffed up it can certainly be done to the weaker ones, but  a lot of the named dragons even CH themselves, since they can't be mezzed and have gargantuan mana pools, it's pretty much impossible. There is also the issue of dispells, a lot of them do this and it can really turn things around before you even have a chance to even dent thier health. Like Klap said, they've even tried it with multiple bards and I'm sure they were thorough, there are just too many variables. Maybe with lvl 70 coming and more new AAs things will change but I doubt it. 
<br />
   If you're looking for Kudos, solo the Trial of Flame or AE some elemental mobs. You could also head to Western Wastes and kill some of those dragons too, or you could try duoing Zlandi like someone mentioned. </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
