				<td colspan="2"><span>for the malto guys who want to try 6 bard groups for tough kills such as the named dragies this is a nifty strategy i thought of...
<br />

<br />
6 bards, load charm, kazam, all 3 of our hp regens, Lev, and what ever else you think of...
<br />

<br />
each bard gets a pet, all bards send pets in at the same time and then first bard starts kazam... won;t matter what the dragon does for 18 seconds, it gets beat up by pets...
<br />

<br />
kazam wears off, first second start to recharm any pets that broke, and anyone else (besides next kazam in row) begins a regen/levitate (for the gflux dragons).  second second next bard starts kazam.  only 4 seconds of combat time with the dragie have elapsed, now every one is divined again with regens on them.  18 seconds of pets beating the dragon down...
<br />

<br />
repeat this cycle until all the bards have divined (18 seconds each, plus 4 seconds between each) using up 2 minutes and 12 seconds minimum (more if there are delays/missed notes between rounds) and no single bard should be too beat up at this point.  Now sustain PoV, lev, regen and try and stay out of melee range as much as you can, if getting summoned too much deft dance for some safety and mem blurr it so it summons someone else.  as soon as kazaad repops complete the cycle again... this way none of the bards see much actual combat to get beat up and 6 pets should tear things up pretty quickly.</span></td>
